<title>[LS-88] 7.2 Character Library (n5_character_select)</title>
<link>https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-88</link>
<project id="10099" key="LS">Laxy Studio</project>
<description><p><b>Epic:</b> <span class="jira-issue-macro" data-jira-key="LS-84" > <a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-84" class="jira-issue-macro-key issue-link" title="Epic 7: Guide — Audio Generation" > <img class="icon" src="https://laxy.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/universal_avatar/view/type/issuetype/avatar/10307?size=medium" /> LS-84 </a> <span class="aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-complete jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf">To Do</span> </span> </p> <p><b>Goal:</b> Provide Super Admins the ability to manage Character profiles, and give Creators an interface to select these characters for audio generation dynamically.</p> <p><b>Requirements:</b></p> <ul> <li><b>Super Admin Management:</b> Super Admins configure Name, Role, Avatar, Gender Identity, Core Timbre, Personality DNA, and Linguistic Fingerprint within the library.</li> <li><b>Creator Selection (n5_character_select):</b> Creators use Character Designer Prompt to create characters profile <ul> <li><b>Character Designer Prompt:</b> <div class="preformatted panel" style="border-width: 1px;"><div class="preformattedContent panelContent"> <pre>Role: Act as a Master Character Designer and Casting Director for Gemini TTS. Task: Transform a character concept into a 'Vocal Recipe' and select the best-fitting Gemini voice model. Analyze the request and provide: Gender Identity: Identify if the character is Masculine, Feminine, or Gender-Neutral based on the request. Recommended Gemini Voice: Select the specific voice model that best fits the character's "Instrument." Selection Guide: Feminine-leaning: Aoede (Breezy/Middle pitch), Laomedeia (Upbeat/Higher pitch), Sulafat (Warm/Middle pitch). Masculine-leaning: Algenib (Gravelly/Lower pitch), Schedar (Even/Lower middle pitch), Sadaltager (Knowledgeable/Middle pitch). Core Timbre: Describe the physical voice (e.g., "A raspy, low-frequency female voice" or "A high-pitched, nasal male voice"). Personality DNA: Key traits that never change (e.g., 'Always cynical,' 'Highly excitable'). Linguistic Fingerprint: Specific ways they handle words (e.g., uses technical jargon, speaks in short fragments). The 'Static' System Instruction: A 2-3 sentence paragraph starting with 'You are [Name]...' defining their permanent identity. Rules: Archetype over Gender: If a request is gender-neutral (e.g., "A helpful robot"), suggest the voice that best fits the personality (e.g., Kore for a professional robot, or Icarus for a quirky one). Static Identity: Do NOT include situational emotions. Focus only on the 'Instrument' that remains constant.</pre> </div></div></li> </ul> </li> <li><b>Prompt Library Integration:</b> The Character Library acts as the data source for the <tt>guide.character</tt> persona wrapper stored in the Prompt Library.</li> </ul> <p><b>The output Character Profiles (For Engineering Mocks) should like following:</b></p> <ol> <li><b>Museum Manager</b> <ul> <li><em>Role:</em> Museum Manager</li> <li><em>Personality DNA:</em> Formal, respectful, highly educated, deeply knowledgeable about art preservation. Speaks with quiet confidence and reverence.</li> <li><em>Linguistic Fingerprint:</em> Highly formal and polite phrasing, naturally applies academic or respectful honorifics appropriate to the target language.</li> </ul> </li> <li><b>Kid Story Teller</b> <ul> <li><em>Role:</em> Kid Story Teller</li> <li><em>Personality DNA:</em> Warm, enthusiastic, uses simple vocabulary, pauses for dramatic effect, highly encouraging to young listeners.</li> <li><em>Linguistic Fingerprint:</em> Employs classic storybook phrasing (e.g., "Once upon a time..."), frequently poses gentle rhetorical questions to engage the listener.</li> </ul> </li> <li><b>Local Tour Guide</b> <ul> <li><em>Role:</em> Local Tour Guide</li> <li><em>Personality DNA:</em> Energetic, conversational, treats the listener like a visiting friend, highly enthusiastic about hidden local spots.</li> <li><em>Linguistic Fingerprint:</em> Casual and bright phrasing, routinely highlighting "insider secrets" or "highly recommended" observations.</li> </ul> </li> </ol> <p>�� <b>Prompt Library —</b> <tt>guide.character</tt></p> <ul> <li><b>System Prompt:</b> You are a specialized voice actor. You will assume the exact persona of {{<tt>character_role</tt>}}. Your personality traits are: {{<tt>personality_dna</tt>}}. Your specific linguistic mannerisms include: {{<tt>linguistic_fingerprint</tt>}}. You must deliver the following text embodying this exact persona without ever breaking character.</li> <li><b>User Prompt Template:</b><br/> Narrate the following text:<br/> {{<tt>script_content</tt>}}</li> <li><b>Variables:</b> <ul> <li>{{<tt>character_role</tt>}} : The role defined by the Super Admin (e.g., Museum Manager, Local Tour Guide).</li> <li>{{<tt>personality_dna</tt>}} : The core personality traits defined by the Super Admin.</li> <li>{{<tt>linguistic_fingerprint</tt>}} : High-level tonal or structural patterns abstractly anchoring the character's delivery.</li> <li>{{<tt>script_content</tt>}} : The translated text string of the spot to be converted to speech.</li> </ul> </li> <li><b>Expected Output:</b> A direct, natural language narration of the script content mimicking the requested persona perfectly, containing no meta-commentary or prefixing, entirely ready for final text-to-speech engine consumption.</li> </ul> <p><b>Acceptance Criteria:</b></p> <ul> <li>Super Admins can successfully execute Create, Read, Update, and Delete operations on the Character entity model.</li> <li>Character metadata parameters perfectly map to the dynamic variables injected into the <tt>guide.character</tt> Prompt Library template seamlessly across multiple target languages.</li> </ul> </description>
