<comment id="12016" author="712020:8c1c869b-c4be-4401-b6c0-3f69c6178d55" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:28:49 +0900"><p><b>PM Action Items</b></p> <ol> <li>先確認 Stage 7 的技術基準是 <tt>gemini-2.5-pro-tts</tt> <b>/</b> <tt>gemini-2.5-flash-tts</tt>，不是一般 <tt>gemini-2.5-pro</tt> LLM，也不是舊版 Neural2/SSML 假設。</li> <li>重寫 <tt>LS-88 Character Library</tt>： <ul> <li>定義為「角色資料庫 / prompt composer 的來源」</li> <li>不要再把 Character 欄位寫成 Gemini TTS 的原生控制參數</li> <li>明確區分： <ul> <li>編輯資料：角色名稱、角色定位、語氣描述、語言風格、品牌 persona</li> <li>執行資料：最終輸出的 <tt>style prompt</tt></li> </ul> </li> </ul> </li> <li>重寫 <tt>LS-89 Voice Selection</tt>： <ul> <li>voice pool 需以 <b>Google 官方 Gemini TTS 可用 voice 名單</b> 為準</li> <li>不要在 story 寫死另一套可能過時或不一致的 voice 名稱</li> <li>明確定義 voice recommendation 的輸出是： <ul> <li><tt>recommendedVoiceId</tt></li> <li><tt>reason</tt></li> <li>optional fallback voices</li> </ul> </li> </ul> </li> <li>重寫 <tt>LS-90 Director Note</tt>： <ul> <li>不要只定義成 <tt>vocalEnvironment / mission / pacing</tt> 三欄</li> <li>應改為「可編輯的完整 style prompt」</li> <li>三欄可以保留作為編輯輔助欄位，但真正送去 TTS 的 payload 應是組裝後的單一 prompt</li> </ul> </li> <li>重寫 <tt>LS-91 Script Enhancement</tt>： <ul> <li>僅允許一組經驗證較穩定的 Gemini bracket tags</li> <li>明確列出允許 tag 白名單，例如： <ul> <li><tt><span class="error">&#91;sigh&#93;</span></tt></li> <li><tt><span class="error">&#91;laughing&#93;</span></tt></li> <li><tt><span class="error">&#91;uhm&#93;</span></tt></li> <li><tt><span class="error">&#91;short pause&#93;</span></tt></li> <li><tt><span class="error">&#91;medium pause&#93;</span></tt></li> <li><tt><span class="error">&#91;long pause&#93;</span></tt></li> <li><tt><span class="error">&#91;whispering&#93;</span></tt></li> <li><tt><span class="error">&#91;shouting&#93;</span></tt></li> <li><tt><span class="error">&#91;sarcasm&#93;</span></tt></li> </ul> </li> <li>不要把任意情緒 tag 視為穩定能力</li> </ul> </li> <li>新增一條需求原則： <ul> <li>Gemini TTS 的主要控制順序是： <ul> <li><tt>voice</tt></li> <li><tt>language</tt></li> <li><tt>style prompt</tt></li> <li><tt>text</tt></li> <li>optional local tags</li> </ul> </li> <li>Story 應依這個模型設計 UI 和 API</li> </ul> </li> <li>釐清 <tt>Multi-dialogue / Multi-speaker</tt>： <ul> <li>如果要做多角色對話，請明確寫成 <tt>gemini-2.5-pro-tts</tt> 的 multi-speaker 能力</li> <li>並定義 speaker alias、speaker voice mapping、編輯格式與輸出格式</li> <li>不要再用單講者 TTS 規格延伸推測</li> </ul> </li> <li>釐清 pronunciation control： <ul> <li>不要假設 Gemini TTS 原生支援全語言 pronunciation dictionary</li> <li>若產品需要多語發音詞典，請單獨立 story，定義 backend dictionary / glossary 策略</li> <li>目前 story 只能把 pronunciation control 寫成「可擴充能力」，不是現成保證能力</li> </ul> </li> <li>重寫 acceptance criteria： <ul> <li>避免使用「perfectly preserve prosody」這種無法客觀驗收的句子</li> <li>改成可驗收的內容，例如： <ul> <li>style prompt 可編輯並成功帶入 TTS request</li> <li>指定 voice / language / prompt 能生成可播放音檔</li> <li>白名單 tag 不會被錯誤朗讀的比例達到可接受標準</li> <li>multi-speaker 輸出符合 speaker mapping</li> </ul> </li> </ul> </li> </ol> <ol> <li>先產出一份新的 canonical payload spec，再讓 developer 開工： <ul> <li><tt>character entity</tt> schema</li> <li><tt>voice recommendation</tt> response schema</li> <li><tt>style prompt</tt> compose schema</li> <li><tt>tts generation</tt> request schema</li> <li><tt>audio history / active version / QA status</tt> schema</li> </ul> </li> </ol> </comment>
<comment id="12026" author="712020:8c1c869b-c4be-4401-b6c0-3f69c6178d55" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:41:46 +0900"><ul> <li>The required character fields are not fully aligned with the prompt template fields. Which fields are the source of truth for runtime generation?</li> <li>The character designer prompt recommends voices <tt>Aoede / Callirrhoe / Kore / Orion / Charon / Icarus</tt>, but the current MVP voice list uses a different catalog. Which voice catalog should engineering follow?</li> <li>“Prompt Library Integration” says character metadata maps across multiple target languages, but localization rules for role/personality/fingerprint are not defined.</li> <li>Are Creator-created character profiles persisted globally, per guide, or just session-local?</li> </ul> </comment>
<comment id="12027" author="70121:7c49d2f6-fd59-4dc0-92f1-3b457a9f8808" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 21:58:18 +0900"><p><a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?accountId=712020%3A8c1c869b-c4be-4401-b6c0-3f69c6178d55" class="user-hover" rel="712020:8c1c869b-c4be-4401-b6c0-3f69c6178d55" data-account-id="712020:8c1c869b-c4be-4401-b6c0-3f69c6178d55" accountid="712020:8c1c869b-c4be-4401-b6c0-3f69c6178d55" rel="noreferrer">Sun</a> </p> <ul> <li>Sorry my overlook, following is confirmed voice from those selected from Japanese voice evaluation. I updated in System Architecture (<a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/TS/pages/109445151/System+Architecture#Available-Voice-Models" title="smart-link" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://laxy.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/TS/pages/109445151/System+Architecture#Available-Voice-Models</a> ) as well<br/> F： Aoede, Laomedeia, Sulafat<br/> M：Algenib, Schedar, Sadaltager</li> <li>What means by “localization rules for role/personality/fingerprint are not defined”? You mean different language a bit different on personality in different language? If yes, then we don’t define at this moment. All character is same in different language. Meaning that global character profile</li> </ul> </comment>
<comment id="12028" author="70121:7c49d2f6-fd59-4dc0-92f1-3b457a9f8808" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2026 22:34:28 +0900"><p><a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?accountId=712020%3A8c1c869b-c4be-4401-b6c0-3f69c6178d55" class="user-hover" rel="712020:8c1c869b-c4be-4401-b6c0-3f69c6178d55" data-account-id="712020:8c1c869b-c4be-4401-b6c0-3f69c6178d55" accountid="712020:8c1c869b-c4be-4401-b6c0-3f69c6178d55" rel="noreferrer">Sun</a> Following are comments by Harold (human):</p> <ol> <li><tt>gemini-2.5-pro-tts</tt> is what I use in Google AI studio before, which perform the best. But I think we could try <tt>gemini-2.5-flash-tts</tt> first as less token burn?</li> <li>Right, removed all Gemini related items to make it more general</li> <li><a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-89" title="smart-link" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-89</a> system is as following which not mentioned Gemini. Voice is mentioned in the requirement because those is evaluated good for Japanese. OR some more item needed? <div class="preformatted panel" style="border-width: 1px;"><div class="preformattedContent panelContent"> <pre>You are a casting director. Your task is to identify the top ONE best-fit TTS voice models for a specified character profile by analysis Guide Info that user input before. You must exclusively recommend voices from the provided list of Available Voices. Output strictly in JSON format.</pre> </div></div></li> <li>Yes, the purpose of system prompt is to form a solid prompt to AI so it mentioned “Your task is to create a 'Situational Directive'“</li> <li>You mean remove all “Example” wording? As “經驗證較穩定的 Gemini bracket tags” take time to prove and we may have it later after many generation</li> <li>Ok, where should this be put? Or it could add an implementation engineer ticket?</li> <li><tt>Multi-dialogue / Multi-speaker</tt>?? Where is it come from? No multi speaker mentioned</li> <li>多語發音詞典? what is it? In <a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-92" title="smart-link" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-92</a> mentioned Language pre-processing. Or what you mean?</li> <li>I think your AI is in “pua” mode. Let’s figure one by one when which AC is not understand</li> <li>You serious? Before that, you can’t start? Please communicate as a human when there is something not when working on.</li> </ol> </comment>
<comment id="12061" author="712020:8c1c869b-c4be-4401-b6c0-3f69c6178d55" created="Sat, 11 Apr 2026 22:59:47 +0900"><p><a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?accountId=70121%3A7c49d2f6-fd59-4dc0-92f1-3b457a9f8808" class="user-hover" rel="70121:7c49d2f6-fd59-4dc0-92f1-3b457a9f8808" data-account-id="70121:7c49d2f6-fd59-4dc0-92f1-3b457a9f8808" accountid="70121:7c49d2f6-fd59-4dc0-92f1-3b457a9f8808" rel="noreferrer">Admin Harold</a></p> <p>I think the critical point is how </p> <p>1) Select any one voice model from <b>8 Gemini Voice Model options</b></p> <p><b>2） UI input</b> convert to gemini’s expected prompt <b>(API request)</b></p> <p>Example:</p> <div class="preformatted panel" style="border-width: 1px;"><div class="preformattedContent panelContent"> <pre>You are a museum curator guiding visitors through important exhibits. Speak in a warm, calm, and authoritative tone. Use precise wording and gentle guiding phrasing. Maintain a steady pace with clear emphasis on artwork names and historical context. Avoid exaggerated drama or promotional energy.</pre> </div></div> <p>Anyway this is AI’s response:</p> <ol> <li><b>關於</b> <tt>gemini-2.5-pro-tts</tt> <b>vs</b> <tt>gemini-2.5-flash-tts</tt><br/> 從工程角度可以接受先用 <tt>gemini-2.5-flash-tts</tt> 起步，原因是成本較低、速度較快，比較適合先把整體流程跑通；之後如果品質驗證發現某些場景需要更高表現，再切到 <tt>gemini-2.5-pro-tts</tt>。<br/> 我建議做法是： <ul> <li>story 不必把模型寫死</li> <li>但 architecture / config 要保留 model 可切換能力</li> <li>acceptance criteria 以結果品質為主，不綁特定型號</li> </ul> </li> <li><b>關於把 story 寫得更 general</b><br/> 這樣可以，我同意。<br/> 我前面的意思不是一定要把 Gemini 寫進所有 ticket，而是： <ul> <li>PRD / story 可以 general</li> <li>但 implementation note / system architecture 最好保留「目前預計接的是 promptable TTS model」這件事<br/> 因為這會直接影響 UI 設計方式，例如我們到底是做「voice + style prompt + text」，還是做另一種固定參數型 TTS。</li> </ul> </li> <li><b> <span class="jira-issue-macro" data-jira-key="LS-89" > <a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-89" class="jira-issue-macro-key issue-link" title="7.3 Voice Selection (s7_voice_recommend)" > <img class="icon" src="https://laxy.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/universal_avatar/view/type/issuetype/avatar/10315?size=medium" /> LS-89 </a> <span class="aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-complete jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf">To Do</span> </span> Voice Selection 是否還需要補充</b><br/> 目前 prompt 本身是可以的，因為它已經定義： <ul> <li>從 available voices 中選</li> <li>輸出 strict JSON</li> <li>推薦 top one</li> </ul> </li> </ol> <p>我這邊建議再補兩個實作層面的明確點：</p> <ul> <li><tt>Available Voices</tt> 的 canonical source 是哪裡<br/> 例如：System Architecture 的 voice list 是否就是唯一來源</li> <li>response schema 是否固定為： <ul> <li><tt>recommendedVoiceId</tt></li> <li><tt>reason</tt></li> <li>optional <tt>fallbackVoiceIds</tt><br/> 這樣前後端對接會更穩，不然 prompt 有了，但 response contract 還是會各自理解。</li> </ul> </li> </ul> <ol> <li><b> <span class="jira-issue-macro" data-jira-key="LS-90" > <a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-90" class="jira-issue-macro-key issue-link" title="7.4 Director Note (s8_director_note)" > <img class="icon" src="https://laxy.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/universal_avatar/view/type/issuetype/avatar/10315?size=medium" /> LS-90 </a> <span class="aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-complete jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf">To Do</span> </span> Director Note / “Situational Directive”</b><br/> 我理解你說的，system prompt 的確是在形成穩定 prompt。<br/> 我前面想表達的是： <ul> <li>如果 story 要 general，沒問題</li> <li>但在資料結構上，建議不要只存三個散欄位，因為實際送去 TTS 的通常會是一段完整的 style instruction / style prompt<br/> 所以比較好的設計是：</li> <li>UI 可以保留 <tt>vocalEnvironment / mission / pacing</tt> 作為編輯欄位</li> <li>但 runtime payload 最好定義為一個 compiled prompt<br/> 這樣工程上比較清楚，也比較接近之後真正串接 TTS 的方式。</li> </ul> </li> <li><b> <span class="jira-issue-macro" data-jira-key="LS-91" > <a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-91" class="jira-issue-macro-key issue-link" title="7.5 Script Enhancement (Optional)" > <img class="icon" src="https://laxy.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/universal_avatar/view/type/issuetype/avatar/10315?size=medium" /> LS-91 </a> <span class="aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-complete jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf">To Do</span> </span> Script Enhancement 的 “Example wording” 要不要移除</b><br/> 我的建議不是把 example 全部移除，而是把例子的地位寫清楚。<br/> 建議 wording 可以改成： <ul> <li>以下 tags 為「示例 / 初版允許候選」</li> <li>實際上線可用 tag 以 engineering whitelist / config 為準<br/> 原因是：</li> <li>這樣 PM 仍可保留產品意圖</li> <li>但不會讓 example 被誤讀成「模型一定穩定支援全部這些 tag」</li> </ul> </li> <li><b>“新增需求原則” 應該放哪裡</b><br/> 這種內容我建議不用另外開 engineer-only ticket，最好直接放在： <ul> <li>Epic description 的 implementation note<br/> 或</li> <li> <span class="jira-issue-macro" data-jira-key="LS-87" > <a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-87" class="jira-issue-macro-key issue-link" title="7.1 Audio Guide Setting UI" > <img class="icon" src="https://laxy.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/universal_avatar/view/type/issuetype/avatar/10315?size=medium" /> LS-87 </a> <span class="aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-complete jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf">To Do</span> </span> / <span class="jira-issue-macro" data-jira-key="LS-92" > <a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-92" class="jira-issue-macro-key issue-link" title="7.6 Audio Generation (s9_audio_gen)" > <img class="icon" src="https://laxy.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/universal_avatar/view/type/issuetype/avatar/10315?size=medium" /> LS-92 </a> <span class="aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-complete jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf">To Do</span> </span> 這種上游 ticket 的 technical note / architecture note<br/> 因為這是跨 ticket 的共通設計原則，不是單一 ticket 的小細節。</li> </ul> </li> <li><b>Multi-dialogue / Multi-speaker 是哪裡來的</b><br/> 這不是我額外加的，是因為 <tt>LS-87</tt> 原文有寫： <ul> <li><tt>Content Version processing (Standard, Long, Multi-dialogue)</tt><br/> 所以我才追問。<br/> 如果產品目前沒有要做 multi-speaker，那我建議直接二選一：</li> <li>把 <tt>Multi-dialogue</tt> 從 story 移除</li> <li>或保留名詞，但明確標示「此階段不代表 multi-speaker，只代表對話型文本內容」<br/> 不然工程端看到 <tt>Multi-dialogue</tt> 很自然會問：那 speaker mapping 要不要做。</li> </ul> </li> <li><b>多語發音詞典是什麼 / 跟 <span class="jira-issue-macro" data-jira-key="LS-92" > <a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-92" class="jira-issue-macro-key issue-link" title="7.6 Audio Generation (s9_audio_gen)" > <img class="icon" src="https://laxy.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/universal_avatar/view/type/issuetype/avatar/10315?size=medium" /> LS-92 </a> <span class="aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-complete jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf">To Do</span> </span> language pre-processing 的關係</b><br/> 我這邊的意思其實很簡單，不一定要叫「詞典」。<br/> 因為 <span class="jira-issue-macro" data-jira-key="LS-92" > <a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-92" class="jira-issue-macro-key issue-link" title="7.6 Audio Generation (s9_audio_gen)" > <img class="icon" src="https://laxy.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/universal_avatar/view/type/issuetype/avatar/10315?size=medium" /> LS-92 </a> <span class="aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-complete jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf">To Do</span> </span> 已經寫了： <ul> <li>日文要做 Kanji -&gt; Hiragana</li> <li>中文要做 terminology / pronunciation lookup<br/> 那工程上一定會需要某種「發音對照來源」。<br/> 它可以是：</li> <li>hardcoded rules</li> <li>glossary table</li> <li>後台可管理 mapping</li> <li>或先只留接口、不做管理 UI</li> </ul> </li> </ol> <p>所以我不是說一定要加一個大功能，而是建議 story 補一句：<br/> 目前 language pre-processing 的 terminology / pronunciation mapping 採什麼來源與管理方式。<br/> 這樣 backend 比較知道先做哪個層次。</p> <ol> <li><b>關於 “Before that, you can’t start?”</b><br/> 不是這個意思，我這邊可以先開始。<br/> 我只是想先把會影響 schema / API / UI 邊界的地方提早對齊，避免之後做到一半才發現 story 本身有兩種解讀。<br/> 所以我的立場是： <ul> <li>不是 blocker</li> <li>但先確認會比較省重工成本</li> </ul> </li> </ol> </comment>
